  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop the <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;finely</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably nonstick) with a matching lid on a medium heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> (optional)</p>\r\n<p>When hot, add the <strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8 min or until softened and brown at the edges, stirring occasionally</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) or grate the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and chop the <strong>garlic</strong> finely (or grate)</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> to a <strong>pestle and mortar</strong> with 1 tsp of <strong>salt</strong> (or pulse in a food processor)</p>\r\n<p>Bash to a coarse <strong>paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>paste</strong> to the <strong>onions</strong> with the <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong> and <strong>cinnamon</strong>, and cook for 2 min on a medium heat, stirring as you go to coat the onions evenly</p>\r\n<p>Tip: add a drizzle of <strong>oil</strong> if the spices look too dry</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for a further 1 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/440_step-3-x400.jpg",
